REC WAF 2023 ACTIVITY TRACKER ANALYSIS

Author

RECWAF PMEL Team

1 Number of Activities

Majority of the activities done from January 2023 till date are related to training and capacity building.

Sierra Leone and Ghana has conducted the most diverse activities. Mostly training in Ghana and sensitisation in Sierra Leone.

7 Sensitisation

Similar to direct beneficiaries, sensitizations carried out in Nigeria, Ghana, and Sierra Leone presently have almost equal proportion of estimated reach of males and females.

The sensitization campaigns have focused mostly on land policies, sanitation, gender issues, and promoting fruit and vegetables as a business

8 Campaigns

Presently, no Campaigns have been carried out in the REC

9 VSLA Engagements

Since January, a total of 38 VSLA engagements have been executed, most of which were done under the Better Chicken project in Ghana.

The VSLA reports submitted so far for this year are mostly pertaining to VSLA Activity tracking.

Backstopping was the most prevalent form of assistance provided to VSLAs during facilitation visits by both the Cocoalife and Better Chicken projects.
